# Security & Authentication

## Password Storage
- **NEVER** store passwords in plain text - always use **BCrypt** or **Argon2**

## JWT Tokens
- Use **JWT tokens** for authentication with proper expiration
- Implement **refresh tokens** for long-lived sessions
- Store JWT secret in **environment variables** or **Azure Key Vault**, never in code

## Input Validation
- Validate **all user input** on the server side
- Implement **rate limiting** to prevent abuse
- Don't trust user input - always validate and sanitize

## HTTPS & CORS
- Use **HTTPS** in production (add HSTS header)
- Implement **CORS** properly - don't use `AllowAnyOrigin` in production

## Email Verification
- Generate **cryptographically secure** challenge keys
- Set **expiration time** for verification links (24 hours)
- Store challenge keys **hashed** in the database
